The Core Structure

Adaptive governance is built on:

5 sequential capacities + 1 meta-capacity

These are not parallel.

They must be built in order.

The Capacities

1. Ownership Continuity
Passages are identified and owned
→ Without it: Vacuum (no one owns the crossing)

2. Signal Preservation
Signals move intact across transitions
→ Without it: Suppression (signal never arrives)

3. Threshold Stewardship
Crossings governed by neutral parties
→ Without it: Capture (interested parties distort outcomes)

4. Friction Calibration
Right amount of governance resistance
→ Without it: Leakage or paralysis

5. Passage Repair
Transitions are fixed when they degrade
→ Without it: recursive failure

6. Passage Learning (Meta-Capacity)
System redesigns passages from failure
→ Without it: systemic brittleness

The Key Insight

These capacities are developmental, not optional.

You cannot:

preserve signals without ownership
govern thresholds without signal integrity
calibrate friction without neutral crossings
repair what you don’t govern
learn without repair

Skipping levels produces fake governance.

The Maturity Model

Organizations progress through six levels:

Level 1 — Ownership
Passages are named

Level 2 — Signal Fidelity
Signals arrive intact

Level 3 — Governed Thresholds
Neutral stewardship exists

Level 4 — Calibrated Movement
Friction matches stakes

Level 5 — Adaptive Repair
Failures trigger passage correction

Level 6 — Generative Learning
Failures redesign the system

The Hardest Capacity: Friction Calibration

Not all friction is bad.

Load-bearing friction:

slows high-risk crossings
prevents distortion
protects signal integrity

Decorative friction:

creates paperwork
adds cost
does no governance work

Most systems:

remove useful friction
keep useless friction

That inversion produces both Capture and Saturation.

Threshold Intelligence (Bridge Capacity)

The difference between reacting and anticipating:

Passage Repair → fixes after failure
Threshold Intelligence → adjusts before failure

This is what separates:

resilient systems
generative systems
